hopobject.body: I'll send you a text prescription drugs for oral herpes Enter a new study from Tufts University. For this experiment, a team of biologists trained the tiny worms (just 1 cm each) to find food hidden in the center of a rough-bottomed petri dish. The meal was lit up by a bright beam of light. Since planarians prefer to skulk around the outskirts where it's dark, this helped ensure that the worms were learning new behaviors.
